      "content": "that's a pretty strong take. some people argue that you can't really plan for state-building mid-war and that the priority HAS to be stopping the humanitarian crisis first or else it's even worse. aren't they right? like, isn't the 'flaw' you're describing just a necessary trade-off to save lives in the moment?",
